  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Gupta et al. [556] proposed a programming language correction framework that uses reinforcement learning to assist novice programmers with syntactic errors.",
    "This framework outperforms their previous work DeepFix [550] in 2017.",
    "Wu et al. [557] trained a deep learning model on the DeepFix dataset.",
    "The model, called graph-based grammar fix, combines token sequences and graph structures based on ASTs to predict the error position and generate correct tokens.",
    "To integrate program-feedback graphs and a self-supervised learning framework, Yasunaga et al. [558] proposed DrRepair, a program repair technique based on graph attention networks.With the rapid development of deep learning, the effectiveness of automatic program repair has been further improved."
  ],
